dcterms:description: The Atari Learning Environment is a platform for evaluating general agents in various Atari games, providing a diverse set of environments for reinforcement learning research.

dcterms:description: The Maze dataset is part of the OpenAI Gym, which provides a variety of environments for testing reinforcement learning algorithms, including a maze environment for pathfinding tasks.
dcterms:title: Maze

dcterms:description: CartPole is a classic control problem where the goal is to balance a pole on a cart by moving the cart left or right. It is included in the OpenAI Gym for testing reinforcement learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: CartPole

dcterms:description: Acrobot is a two-link robot that must swing up to a certain height. It is part of the OpenAI Gym and is used for testing reinforcement learning algorithms.
dcterms:title: Acrobot
